# Key Features

## 1. Smart Task Breakdown
Users break tasks into steps. The most critical step is highlighted first.

## 2. Time-Aware Scheduling
Office hours, free time, and task constraints are considered.

## 3. Cognitive Reinforcement
Users type tasks in their own words to reinforce memory.

## 4. Attention Lock
Task-related questions must be answered to access distractions.

## 5. Emergency Passes
Two free passes per task for genuine emergencies.

## 6. Multi-Task Management
Supports multiple tasks with intelligent prioritization.

## 7. Persistent Notifications
Permanent reminders remain until completion or deadline expiry.
